ay choose to delay doing so until the invocation is passed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the "},{"code":"remoteCall","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". This decision largely depends on if serialization is allowed to happen"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on the caller’s task, and if any smarter encoding can be used once all parameter calls have been"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"recorded (e.g. it may be possible to run-length encode values of certain types etc.)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once encoded, the system should use some underlying transport mechanism to send the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"bytes serialized by the invocation to the remote peer."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Decoding an invocation","anchor":"Decoding-an-invocation"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since every actor system is going to deal with a concrete invocation type, they may"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implement decoding them whichever way is most optimal for the given system."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once decided, the invocation must be passed to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"executeDistributedTarget"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"which will decode the substitutions, argument values, return and error types (in that order).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that the decoding will be provided the specific types that the sending side used to preform the call,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"so decoding can rely on simply invoking e.g. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Codable"},{"text":" (if that is the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SerializationRequirement"},{"text":") decoding","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"entry points on the provided types.","